{
  "stem": "3341.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't look there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were between the very first firms who were nationalized.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Slovakia is an independent country, was a satellite of Germany, if not officially declared.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they were completely under the control of German administration.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not visible German, but everywhere in the very important ministries there were always some Germans who'd keep an eye on them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I-- we-- our firm, because of the importance of economical and the size of it, was important firm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they started-- in 1939 they started to put the major firms-- it doesn't matter what sort of business-- they put, like, trustees of the government, which were known Jewish people, because most of the businesses in Slovakia, especially the big one and the medium-sized one, they're in Jewish hands.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was very hardly a non-Jewish shop, let's say, in a small town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were-- there were only Jewish shops.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In a big city like Bratislava, which was the capital town, of course, there, I would say 1/3 were non-Jewish. 2/3 were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every leading manufacturer, or wholesaler-- the very important businesses-- were all in Jewish hands.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now the government followed the dictatorship of Germany, and they want it to eliminate it, or change it as soon as possible.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because in Germany, or in the protectorate-- in Prague and Moravia, which was converted and occupied by Germany-- Jews were sent out straightaway.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were either sent to the concentration camps, or they were dismissed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And only mostly German people took over the existing firms.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Bratislava, they didn't take such severe methods, because the Slovaks didn't have enough able people to do that, first of all.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not that they liked the Jews, so they left them there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was economically not possible.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
